1
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:19,600
<i>NARRATOR". A world under siege!</i>

2
00:00:19,645 --> 00:00:21,761
<i>The Separatists have launched
a massive offensive</i>

3
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,596
<i>against the planet Ryloth.</i>

4
00:00:23,941 --> 00:00:27,104
<i>A blockade of deadly battleships
has cut off any support</i>

5
00:00:27,194 --> 00:00:29,401
<i>for the dwindling Republic defenses.</i>

6
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:31,107
<i>Though they have fought valiantly</i>

7
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:34,069
<i>with the help of
Twi'|ek freedom fighter Cham Syndulla,</i>

8
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:39,654
<i>hope is fading for Jedi Master Di
and his men as the droid army closes in.</i>

9
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:03,681
Master Jedi!

10
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:05,513
We're running out of food and water,

11
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:07,974
and our heavy weapons systems
are out of power.

12
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:10,484
I'll contact our forces in orbit.

13
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:14,989
Admiral Dao, this is General Di.
We're in trouble down here.

14
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:17,066
We need those supplies immediately.

15
00:01:18,704 --> 00:01:22,493
I understand, General,
but I am in no position to help.

16
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,166
We are critically low
on fuel and ammunition.

17
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,584
<i>Contact the Jedi Council again!</i>

18
00:01:27,671 --> 00:01:30,789
<i>Tell them reinforcements
must be dispatched without delay!</i>

19
00:01:37,431 --> 00:01:41,516
<i>if help does not arrive soon, the entire
Outer Rim garrison will be wiped out.</i>

20
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,516
Surely there must be
something you can do...

21
00:01:43,604 --> 00:01:46,437
<i>The main reactor's been hit, sir.
Systems are shutting down.</i>

22
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:48,480
<i>We are dead in space.</i>

23
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:51,025
<i>With regret, I report that
my fleet will no longer be able</i>

24
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,694
<i>to provide protection for
the troops on Ryloth.</i>

25
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:56,606
<i>I repeat my request
that help be sent right</i> away.

26
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:58,611
<i>The shields are gone! We have no...</i>

27
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:06,699
Trapped on Ryloth,
Master Di and his men are.

28
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:14,458
My trade mission was successful.
Thank you for asking.

29
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:17,259
But what's the matter?
You all look very somber.

30
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:21,305
<i>Senator, the fleet protecting Ryloth
has been destroyed,</i>

31
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:23,632
<i>and the supply lines have been cut.</i>

32
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:27,391
<i>The troops are out of food,
fuel, ammunition,</i>

33
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:29,643
<i>and the civilian population is starving.</i>

34
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:31,315
That is grim news.

35
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:34,393
<i>Our blockade runners should be able
to penetrate the Separatist lines</i>

36
00:02:34,446 --> 00:02:36,403
<i>and drop relief supplies,</i>

37
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:39,653
<i>but they do not have the range
to reach Ryloth.</i>

38
00:02:39,743 --> 00:02:44,078
<i>The planet Toydaria is 2,000 parsecs closer
than the nearest fleet.</i>

39
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:46,405
<i>If the blockade runners
can supply from there,</i>

40
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,366
<i>they might reach Ryloth in time.</i>

41
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:50,034
What would you have me do?

42
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:54,126
<i>We've dispatched a ship loaded with
relief supplies to meet you on Toydaria.</i>

43
00:02:54,216 --> 00:02:55,752
<i>You are a more experienced diplomat</i>

44
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:58,463
<i>than the representative from Naboo
who is already there.</i>

45
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:01,921
Senator Amidala is
an excellent negotiator. I am sure...

46
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:04,552
<i>Senator Amidala
could not leave the Senate.</i>

47
00:03:04,643 --> 00:03:07,726
<i>Representative Binks
accompanied the shipment.</i>

48
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:11,605
<i>You must negotiate the treaty so that
we can dispatch ships from Toydaria</i>

49
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:14,024
<i>and get Ryloth the relief supplies it needs.</i>

50
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,693
I understand perfectly.

51
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:30,995
This had better be important.

52
00:03:31,086 --> 00:03:33,794
Sir, we intercepted a coded transmission

53
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,747
between Senator Organa
and the Jedi Council.

54
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:40,005
We were able to partially unscramble it.

55
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:46,175
The Jedi have sent Senator Organa
to Toydaria to negotiate a treaty,

56
00:03:46,268 --> 00:03:50,227
which would allow them to send
relief supplies to their forces on Ryloth.

57
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:54,147
Send a message to Senator Lott Dod
of the Trade Federation.

58
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:57,101
I wish to speak with him immediately.

59
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,937
Stop where you are, offworlder.

60
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:37,016
We will provide you whatever you need
to continue yourjourney,

61
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:38,692
but you may not leave this ship.

62
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:42,279
I am Senator Bail Organa
of the Galactic Republic.

63
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:46,029
I come to speak with
the High Exalted King of Toydaria.

64
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:47,780
Hi-I0!

65
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:51,409
Let meesa through!
Meesa on a diplomatic mission.

66
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:55,164
Senator Organa!
ltsa pleasure to be seeing yousa.

67
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:58,336
And you, Representative Binks. Shall we?

68
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:01,666
Our laws of hospitality
demand that we offer assistance,

69
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,092
but this planet is closed to offworlders.

70
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:07,763
We are obliged to deliver our message
to your king in person.

71
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,931
It won't take a minute.

72
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:22,649
Hi-lo? Yousa Majesty?

73
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:24,480
Let me do the talking, okay?

74
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,912
State your business, offworlders.

75
00:05:36,378 --> 00:05:39,166
Representative Binks of Naboo.

76
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:43,591
Senator Bail Organa of Alderaan, sire.
We have come to ask for your help.

77
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:47,762
Perhaps you failed to pay attention
to the Senate orientation.

78
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:51,591
They should have explained
that Toydaria is a neutral system.

79
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,847
We are not part of the Republic.

80
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:55,973
Yes, Your Majesty.

81
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:59,056
That is why we have come before you
as friends.

82
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:01,817
There is a humanitarian crisis on Ryloth.

83
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:05,066
Millions will be starving and dying
without your help.

84
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:08,448
My esteemed colleague and I humbly beg

85
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:11,493
that you allow us to use Toydaria
as a staging ground

86
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,742
to supply the planet with relief aid.

87
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:17,916
Do not make your decision in haste,
Your Majesty.

88
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:21,875
There are other factors
you might wish to consider.

89
00:06:33,977 --> 00:06:38,187
I believe you know Lott Dod,
Senator for the Trade Federation.

90
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:41,482
Yes, we are acquainted. Senator.

91
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:45,607
Begging Your Highness,
whatsa he doing here?

92
00:06:45,655 --> 00:06:47,271
Why shouldn't he be?

93
00:06:47,324 --> 00:06:50,817
Toydaria has an important contract
with his Trade Federation.

94
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:55,121
The Trade Federation is too chummy
with the Separatists for my taste.

95
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:57,657
We have nothing to do
with the Separatists!

96
00:06:57,709 --> 00:06:59,950
Nute Gunray is an extremist.

97
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:03,212
His views do not reflect
those of the Trade Federation.

98
00:07:03,298 --> 00:07:06,666
Perhaps not.
But you can understand the confusion.

99
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:10,677
We are only here to ensure that
nothing jeopardizes the agreement

100
00:07:10,722 --> 00:07:13,510
between Toydaria
and the Trade Federation.

101
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:17,685
Naboo and Alderaan have a long tradition
of providing humanitarian aid.

102
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:20,767
-I see no reason for conflict.
-Nor do I.

103
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:23,561
The people of Ryloth are suffering,

104
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:26,894
and compassion
is a sacred Toydarian value.

105
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,940
Honesty is also a Toydarian value, is it not?

106
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:36,746
I'm sure the Senator mentioned
the Separatist blockade around Ryloth.

107
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:39,698
A blockade? ls this true?

108
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,378
Yes, Your Majesty, but it changes nothing.

109
00:07:48,051 --> 00:07:50,292
It changes everything.

110
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:54,551
If the Separatists are blockading the planet
and we help the Republic,

111
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,886
it will destroy our neutrality.

112
00:07:57,018 --> 00:08:01,228
I must convene my ministers,
then we shall hear your arguments.

113
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,636
General Di, the right flank has collapsed.

114
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,756
The droids will be closing in
on our position.

115
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,762
What about reinforcements?

116
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:41,890
Communication has been spotty.

117
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,772
I promise you, Cham,
the Republic will not abandon Ryloth.

118
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,107
I've heard enough of your promises, Jedi.

119
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:53,481
The fact remains, if we stay here without
reinforcements, we're all going to die.

120
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:55,698
Gobi, tell the people we're leaving.

121
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:56,991
Yes, sir.

122
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:58,614
I don't think you understand.

123
00:08:58,747 --> 00:09:01,364
The right flank has collapsed.
There's no leaving.

124
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,745
We're stuck here together.

125
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:10,381
We will now hear arguments
in the matter of using Toydarian territory

126
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:15,212
to aid the shipment of relief supplies
to the citizens of Ryloth.

127
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:18,718
-Senator Organa.
-Thank you, Your Majesty.

128
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:22,972
The operation the Republic proposes
is purely humanitarian.

129
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:27,439
We wish to deliver food and
medical supplies to the people of Ryloth.

130
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:33,480
But if you won't listen to me, wise king,
listen to Senator Orn Free Taa of Ryloth,

131
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:36,816
who is well aware
of the suffering of his people.

132
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:41,780
<i>Your Highness, our cities lie in ruins.</i>

133
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:48,168
<i>Our transportation hubs are all but
destroyed, so I cannot return home.</i>

134
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:50,211
<i>Our crops burn.</i>

135
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:57,045
<i>The Twi'lek people are starving,
and they will die if no aid comes to them.</i>

136
00:09:58,181 --> 00:10:01,264
<i>I appeal to you, great king.</i>

137
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:10,441
The basic tenets of our morality,
and even our constitution,

138
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:12,939
demand that we help those in need.

139
00:10:13,029 --> 00:10:17,023
Those ideals are noble,
but we must be careful

140
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:20,196
that our compassion does not
draw us into this war.

141
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,698
Senator Dod, if you please.

142
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:27,867
Great king,
Senator Organa is deceiving you.

143
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:34,666
The inconvenient fact remains that
this is a war, and Ryloth is a battlefield.

144
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:40,797
The planet is under a Separatist blockade
because Jedi Knights and clone soldiers

145
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:44,599
are battling the droid army
for control of the surface.

146
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,594
This will not be a humanitarian base.

147
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:50,351
It will be a military base.

148
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:54,815
The Separatist Senate will see it
as a violation of your neutrality.

149
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:58,568
That, in turn, will expose
the Trade Federation's ships

150
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,566
to attacks from the Separatists

151
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:07,248
and force us to cease trade with Toydaria,
a situation desirable to no one.

152
00:11:12,714 --> 00:11:17,504
Your Majesty, the people of Ryloth
did not ask to be invaded.

153
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:20,586
Do not let them suffer
because war came to them.

154
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:23,589
I sympathize with
the plight of the Twi'|eks,

155
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:28,553
but this is not about saving them when
they are fighting against the Separatists.

156
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:30,933
Thank you, Senators.

157
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,516
You have given us much to consider.

158
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:37,645
I will summon you
once I have made my decision.

159
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:42,156
Come on, hurry, hurry!

160
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:47,453
Captain, is the gunship ready?

161
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:51,036
Yes, sir, but it's too small
to evacuate the refugees.

162
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:54,119
No escape? But our families are with us.

163
00:11:55,632 --> 00:11:59,341
If we reconfigure the fuel system,
we can turn the ship

164
00:11:59,469 --> 00:12:03,258
into a bomb big enough
to collapse the pass, here.

165
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:09,052
The enemy will then only be able to
engage us on one front, from this ravine.

166
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:10,852
While we provide cover,

167
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:15,228
the Twi'leks will have time to escape
with the families over the mountain.

168
00:12:15,318 --> 00:12:18,811
Brilliant strategy, General.
I'll go tell the men.

169
00:12:23,785 --> 00:12:28,200
After considerable debate,
I have made my decision.

170
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:30,656
I am sorry, Senator Organa.

171
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:35,290
But for the sake of my people,
Toydaria must remain neutral.

172
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:40,298
A wise ruling, Your Majesty.

173
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,432
That did not go well.

174
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:51,851
What are weesa gonna do now?

175
00:12:51,938 --> 00:12:53,303
My friends.

176
00:12:56,651 --> 00:13:00,565
Toydaria cannot turn a blind eye
to the suffering of Ryloth.

177
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:04,865
The Twi'leks are innocent victims
caught between the warring factions

178
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,491
through no fault of their own.

179
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:10,203
I'm glad you agree, Your Highness.
What are you prepared to do?

180
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:14,625
You may use Toydaria to transfer
the supplies you brought with you.

181
00:13:14,711 --> 00:13:17,453
That's only enough food for one,
maybe two rotations.

182
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:19,458
It will have to do.

183
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:21,039
And you must guarantee

184
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:25,294
that the Trade Federation will not be able
to link Toydaria to the mission.

185
00:13:25,388 --> 00:13:28,722
Agreed. I have an idea.

186
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:37,932
I'll signal you
when the ships are ready to depart.

187
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:40,650
Meesa won't let you down, Senator.

188
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,738
We're pleased you could join us, Senator.

189
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:53,246
-Your Majesty.
-The pleasure is mine.

190
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:56,124
Formal dinners are so tedious.

191
00:13:56,836 --> 00:14:01,546
I'm afraid that pressing matters require me
to make immediate contact with Alderaan.

192
00:14:01,591 --> 00:14:06,461
But I leave you in the capable hands
of my colleague, Representative Binks.

193
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:19,435
General, we're loading the rest of
the explosives onto the gunship.

194
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:22,272
Very good, Captain. Ready the men.

195
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:24,854
All units, prepare for attack!

196
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:27,860
We won't be able
to hold off the droids for long.

197
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:31,818
You'll have to move quickly
to get your families out of danger.

198
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:39,034
Cham is still angry. He feels betrayed.

199
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:43,543
He counted on Republic assistance,
and it didn't come.

200
00:14:43,633 --> 00:14:48,844
War turns promises into hopes.
I wish it wasn't so.

201
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:51,388
-Tell him.
-I will.

202
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:04,685
Captain Keeli, tell the pilots
to move the gunship into position.

203
00:15:04,821 --> 00:15:08,234
This is Command.
Are all the charges in place?

204
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:11,533
Copy that. We're all ready.
The droid army is closing.

205
00:15:11,661 --> 00:15:15,029
<i>As soon as they are in range,
blow up the gunship.</i>

206
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:26,506
There is a gunship blocking our way.
OM-5, OM-7, go check it out.

207
00:15:26,551 --> 00:15:28,667
Roger, roger.

208
00:15:34,851 --> 00:15:38,060
Careful. It might be full of clones.

209
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,556
No clones, just explosives.

210
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,061
Explosives?

211
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:45,358
Gotcha!

212
00:16:00,877 --> 00:16:04,086
Halt, halt! We cannot get through.

213
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:06,705
We will have to find another way around.

214
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:27,226
Move those supplies into the transport
as soon as possible.

215
00:16:35,161 --> 00:16:38,244
<i><i>Repeat. The ships are ready to launch.</i>

216
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:44,250
Uh, lookie, lookie!

217
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:50,124
Meesa proposing a conceptual work of art

218
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:53,422
to honor the ambassador
of Trade Federation.

219
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:55,925
Let's see, I'll take that one. Mmm-hmm.

220
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,088
Uh-oh.

221
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:05,435
Yeah, just give me... You done with that?
That's really good.

222
00:17:05,525 --> 00:17:08,483
I heard Toydarians really like that,
but I'm taking it.

223
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,810
Thank you very much.
I'm sure you're finished with that.

224
00:17:10,905 --> 00:17:14,148
Did you enjoy that? Did you like that one?
Well, I'll take it, thank you.

225
00:17:15,493 --> 00:17:19,327
Uh...
Excuse me. Thank you. I'll take that.

226
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:24,992
Gentlemen and...gentlemen.

227
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:26,417
Here, let's try this one.

228
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,581
You thought I was going to drop...

229
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,757
I... Here we go!

230
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:41,803
Whoo!

231
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:53,394
Spinning. One, two, three! Ah!

232
00:17:54,115 --> 00:17:56,652
Thank you very much.
That is conceptual art piece.

233
00:17:56,701 --> 00:17:58,237
Thank you.

234
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:04,831
Meesa just sharing my Gungan art
with yousa and...

235
00:18:07,378 --> 00:18:08,960
And meesa.

236
00:18:09,005 --> 00:18:10,837
What are you looking at?

237
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,255
Meesa look at nothing.
No, no, no. Meesa look at nothing.

238
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:17,051
Meesa creating and sharing

239
00:18:17,138 --> 00:18:21,507
Gungan ritual-style art
with Trade Federation

240
00:18:24,186 --> 00:18:27,099
to promote love and understanding.

241
00:18:33,696 --> 00:18:38,156
Steady. Remember, we have to buy
as much time for the Twi'leks <i>as</i> possible.

242
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,440
Yes, sir.

243
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:45,030
For the Republic! For the Twi'|eks!

244
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:37,089
- Captain Keeli!
-I'm not finished yet, sir.

245
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:39,421
- We can do this, General.

246
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:45,090
Well, let's make the end memorable.

247
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:54,649
This is
Republic blockade runner O-niner-niner.</i>

248
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,442
<i>We have broken through.</i>

249
00:19:57,071 --> 00:20:00,689
The Twi'|eks will live to fight another day.

250
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:10,118
<i>The supplies have arrived at the drop point.</i>

251
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:28,975
It's food and medical supplies
from the Republic!

252
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:41,275
Safe journey, my friends.

253
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:45,533
I hope when we meet again,
it is under more pleasant circumstances.

254
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:46,822
Stop right there!

255
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:52,123
You look pale, Senator.

256
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:54,034
I have just received information

257
00:20:54,128 --> 00:20:58,292
that a fleet of Republic ships has
penetrated the blockade around Ryloth.

258
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:03,130
If the Trade Federation
has proof of any treaty violation,

259
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:05,671
you are welcome to present it
to the full Senate.

260
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:08,632
It takes years for the Senate
to decide anything.

261
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:25,945
You play a dangerous game, Organa.
Next time, you will not get away with this.

262
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:29,861
The Republic has heart, my friend,

263
00:21:29,914 --> 00:21:33,782
but I am not convinced
it has the strength to prevail.

264
00:21:33,876 --> 00:21:37,244
However, after what I witnessed
here today,

265
00:21:37,379 --> 00:21:40,713
perhaps it is time
I reconsidered our neutrality.

266
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:43,591
Tell the Jedi
I am open to meeting with them.

267
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:46,461
Master Yoda will be glad to hear it.

268
00:21:46,889 --> 00:21:50,723
For now, at least,
the people of Ryloth shall endure.

269
00:22:29,723 --> 00:22:30,713
English - SDH

